page.title: 03ROUND ISLAND NEAR ARNE
page.content: Round Island is to the East of the Arne Peninsula. Vegetation on the island consists mainly of trees, especially pine trees. One of the warden's jobs is to clear the needles. No cultivation is practised on the island due to the peacock population. Saltings are located between Round and Long island where black-headed gulls have their breeding grounds. Unfortunately eggs are taken illegally because they are a delicacy and cost about 25p each. The main large house was built by Major Laurence for his daughter Lady Illisse in 1935 on the S.E. side. There are also four other cottages on the island; one, on the N.W. side is Ceder Wood Cottage where Thomas Beecham wrote his "Life of Delius."
